Title: Series: Life of the Virgin
Description: Gothic ornamental framework inset with two arched scenes below and two roundels above; lower left, Pentecost; lower right, Death of the Virgin; top left, Presentation in the temple; top right, the flight into Egypt. 1507 Woodcut
Producer name: Print made by: Jacob Cornelisz. van Oostsanen
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of seven, for comment see 1877,0609.107.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (6)
Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (88)
Steinbart 1937 / Das Holzschnittwerk des Jakob Cornelisz von Amsterdam (6)
Exhibition history: 2014 Mar-Jun, Alkmaar, Stedelijk Museum, Van Oostsanen (1470-1533): Early Dutch Masters,
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Capt Edward G Spencer-Churchill
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: John Rushout, 2nd Baron Northwick
Acquisition notes: 1919,0616.1 to 133 were all purchased from Captain Spencer-Churchill at Northwick Park through his solicitors, Messrs Johnson, Raymond-Barker Co, for a total of £655. The collection had been formed by John Rushout, 2nd Baron Northwick in the 1820s, and had descended to Captain Spencer-Churchill. The earlier provenance of many of the prints is recorded in individual catalogue records.
